This folder contains a collection of R-based projects completed for MAS342 (Data analytics with R). Each project explores core data analysis concepts, including regression modeling, correlation, and applied exploratory techniques.

Projects Included:
Cities Analysis: Cleaned and analyzed population and cost-of-living data to uncover trends across major cities.

Employee Attrition Model: Used logistic regression to identify key drivers of employee turnover.

Regression + Correlation: Investigated relationships between variables using visual and statistical methods, including correlation matrices and linear regression.

Salary Regression Model: Built and evaluated a linear model to predict employee salary based on education, experience, and department.
